<subSubSection lastPageId="60" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="59.[151,1436,1945,2011]" lastBlockId="60.[151,1435,152,216]" lastPageId="60" lastPageNumber="61" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1945,1971]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Absolon &amp; Hrabe" authorityYear="1930" box="[330,559,1946,1971]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Marifugia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cavatica">
<emphasis box="[330,559,1946,1971]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Marifugia cavatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique in being the world's only fresh-water serpulid, of presumably marine origin (
<bibRefCitation author="Sket, B." box="[327,450,1985,2011]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" pagination="102 - 104" refId="ref67509" refString="Sket, B. (1983) Je Marifugia res ubeznik iz morja? [Is Marifugia really a fugitive from the sea?], Proteus, 46, 102 - 104." type="journal article" year="1983">Sket 1983</bibRefCitation>
), inhabiting subterranean waters of the Dinaric karst of the former 
<collectingCountry box="[1244,1378,1985,2011]" name="Serbia" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Yugoslavia</collectingCountry>
. The most recent study (Kupriyanova 
<emphasis box="[534,592,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">et al.</emphasis>
, in prep.) summarises data on ecology, distribution, and reproduction of the species and shows its close relationship with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Southern" authorityYear="1921" box="[724,877,191,216]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Ficopomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[724,877,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Ficopomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,267,332]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName authority="Absolon &amp; Hrabe, 1930" authorityName="Absolon &amp; Hrabe" authorityYear="1930" box="[151,690,267,294]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Marifugia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="cavatica">
<emphasis box="[151,380,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Marifugia cavatica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Absolon, K. &amp; Hrabe, S." box="[392,690,267,294]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="249 - 264" refId="ref55162" refString="Absolon, K. &amp; Hrabe, S. (1930) Uber einen neuen Susswasser - Polychaeten aus den Hohlengewassern der Herzegowina. Zoologischer Anzeiger, Leipzig, 88, 9 / 10, 249 - 264." type="journal article" year="1930">Absolon &amp; Hrabĕ, 1930</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[706,1006,268,294]" name="Bosnia and Herzegovina" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Bosnia and Herzegovina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1022,1111,268,294]" name="Croatia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1127,1229,268,294]" name="Slovenia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
to extreme N.E. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,208,306,332]" name="Italy" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Italy</collectingCountry>
; fresh-water subterranean caves.
</paragraph>
